item.title: CVE-2017-17321|2024-08-05T20:51:30.745Z -- huawei%20technologies%20co.%2C%20ltd. -- ensp
item.description: Huawei eNSP software with software of versions earlier than V100R002C00B510 has a buffer overflow vulnerability. Due to the improper validation of specific command line parameter, a local attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the software process abnormal.
